Title : Waynesburg, Indiana
Text : '''Waynesburg''' is an [[unincorporated community]] in [[Decatur County, Indiana]], in the [[United States]].<ref>{{GNIS|445582}}</ref>

==History==
Waynesburg was laid out in 1844.<ref>{{cite book | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7gMUAQAAMAAJ&pg=PA132#v=onepage&q&f=false | title=History of Decatur County, Indiana: Its People, Industries and Institutions | publisher=B.F. Bowen | author=Harding, Lewis Albert | year=1915 | pages=132}}</ref> Waynesburg had a post office between 1854 and 1902.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.postalhistory.com/postoffices.asp?task=display&state=IN&county=Decatur&searchtext=&pagenum=2 | title=Decatur County | publisher=Jim Forte Postal History | accessdate=3 September 2014}}</ref>

